50|$|The Component Detection Algorithm (CODA) is a {{name for}} a type of LC-MS and <b>chemometrics</b> {{software}} algorithm focused on detecting peaks in noisy chromatograms (TIC) often obtained using the electrospray ionization technique.|$|E
50|$|Process {{analytical}} chemistry involves the following sub-disciplines of {{analytical chemistry}}: microanalytical systems, nanotechnology, chemical detection, electrochemistry or electrophoresis, chromatography, spectroscopy, mass spectrometry, process <b>chemometrics,</b> process control, flow injection analysis, ultrasound, and, hanheld sensors.|$|E
